CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1782910144
OL,3,CTrump took in over $1 billion from
OL,4,Ccrypto in first year back in office
OL,6,FUS President Donald Trump took in more
OL,7,Fthan $1 billion (#750 million) from
OL,8,Fhis crypto businesses last year, a
OL,9,Ffederal filing has shown.
OL,11,FCompanies which were startups when he
OL,12,Ftook the oath of office have now
OL,13,Feclipsed in revenue much of his vast
OL,14,Fproperty portfolio that took him
OL,15,Fdecades to build.
OL,17,FFuelling their rise were billionaire
OL,18,Finvestors, plus many have benefited
OL,19,Ffrom the policy moves of Trump's own
OL,20,Fgovernment.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31002
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1782910144
OL,3,CTrump took in over $1 billion from
OL,4,Ccrypto in first year back in office
OL,6,FTrump got more than $500 million (#378
OL,7,Fmillion) from his World Liberty
OL,8,FFinancial business selling new crypto
OL,9,Fproducts, including "governance
OL,10,Ftokens," according to the required
OL,11,Fannual disclosure report with the
OL,12,FOffice of Government Ethics.
OL,14,FIt also showed another crypto
OL,15,Fbusiness, CIC Digital LLC, took in
OL,16,Fmore than $600 million (#453 million)
OL,17,Ffrom sales of souvenir-type "meme"
OL,18,Fcoins stamped with his face.
OL,20,FBoth the tokens and the coins have
OL,21,Fplunged in value since the sales.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31003
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1782910144
OL,3,CTrump took in over $1 billion from
OL,4,Ccrypto in first year back in office
OL,6,FTrump also took in millions last year
OL,7,Ffrom selling Trump-branded bibles,
OL,8,Fsneakers and other small items in
OL,9,Fanother unprecedented move for the
OL,10,Fpresidency. The sale of Trump-branded
OL,11,Fwatches alone brought in $4.7 million
OL,12,F(around #3.5 million).
OL,14,FThe 927-page disclosure report also
OL,15,Fshows how much the President has taken
OL,16,Fin from his two golf resorts in
OL,17,FScotland.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31004
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1782910144
OL,3,CTrump took in over $1 billion from
OL,4,Ccrypto in first year back in office
OL,6,FIt showed Trump Turnberry on the
OL,7,FAyrshire coast generated #23,640,577
OL,8,Fin "hotel and golf related revenue".
OL,9,FTrump International Golf Links in
OL,10,FAberdeenshire recorded an income of
OL,11,F#6,738,799.
OL,13,FBoth properties were reported to be
OL,14,Fvalued at more than 50 million dollars
OL,15,F(#38 million) each.
OL,17,FThe disclosure paints a striking,
OL,18,Falthough incomplete, picture of the
OL,19,Fmassive growth of the president's
OL,20,Fwealth since taking office last
OL,21,FJanuary.
