OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1782910144
OL,3,CTrump took in over $1 billion from
OL,4,Ccrypto in first year back in office
OL,6,FAfter taking office last year, Trump
OL,7,Freversed the Biden administration's
OL,8,Ftough stance on the crypto industry
OL,9,Fand pushed policies friendly to the
OL,10,Findustry.
OL,12,FBut regulators still had some
OL,13,Fconcerns. Before Trump's World Liberty
OL,14,Fbegan selling "governance tokens,"
OL,15,Fthey issued warnings about this new
OL,16,Fkind of crypto asset, saying that
OL,17,Funlike stocks, the tokens offer no
OL,18,Fownership stake in the issuing
OL,19,Fcompany, just voting power on certain
OL,20,Fcorporate polices, and are difficult
OL,21,Fto value.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31009
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1782910144
OL,3,CTrump took in over $1 billion from
OL,4,Ccrypto in first year back in office
OL,6,FBuyers pounced anyway, including a
OL,7,FChinese billionaire who spent $75
OL,8,Fmillion (#56.6 million) on the tokens
OL,9,Fand $200 million (#151 million) on the
OL,10,Fsouvenir coins. In February last year,
OL,11,Fa federal lawsuit charging him with
OL,12,Fduping investors was paused before
OL,13,Fbeing settled for a fine of $10
OL,14,Fmillion (around #7.5 million).
